alea iacta est

alea iacta est ("the di is cast") is a latin phrase attributed by suetonius
(as iacta alea est) to Julius Caesar on january 10, 49 BC as he led his army across the Rubicon river in Northern Italy . With this step, he entered Italy at the head of this army in defiance of the senate and began his long civil war against pompey and the optimates.The phrase has been adopted in Italian (Il dado e tratto), Romanian (Zarurile au fost aruncate).
